<div id="stitle" style="display:none;">Notebook Entry</div>
<dl id="n36208f"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n36" href="#n36208f">N36 (VI.B.29)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n36all.htm#n36208f"> 208(f)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Fig-leaf apron</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources"><font color="green">[Mormonism.]</font> Those who receive their Endowments are buried in the paraphernalia of the inner cult&mdash;cotton drawers, white shoes and stockings, and <mark>the fig-leaf apron</mark> which the neophytes put on as part of the initiation ceremony. <small> Charles W. Ferguson, <a name="CFCT" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CFCT"><cite title="source">The Confusion of Tongues</cite></a> (1928; rpt. May 1929) 391</small></blockquote> </dd></dl>
